        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-25T17:54:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My understanding was that having multiple values in a cell was intended more for \"undo\"-type use cases, rather than for events (eg. the time series data example in the cloud docs uses one row per data point rather than one frequently-updated row with a timestamped cell).  Is that incorrect?  I don\u0027t mind constructing row keys this way, especially if it keeps me from having to worry about someone \"accidentally\" enabling GC.",
      "parentUuid": "511c1415_e088ee4a",
      "revId": "c232da1e628e6935c9eef1e4fcd8fbc910bc3b58",
